@RemoteControlApi_HostAddress = http://localhost:5067

### Send notification (JSON)
POST {{RemoteControlApi_HostAddress}}/api/notifications
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Hello",
  "body": "Test from http file",
  "link": "https://example.com",
  "targetVersion": "1.2.3",
  "fileName": "note.txt",
  "fileBase64": "SGVsbG8gd29ybGQ="
}

### Send notification (multipart form-data)
POST {{RemoteControlApi_HostAddress}}/api/notifications/form
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=MyBoundary

--MyBoundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="title"

Hello from multipart
--MyBoundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="body"

Message body
--MyBoundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="targetVersion"

1.2.3
--MyBoundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="file"; filename="note.txt"
Content-Type: text/plain

< note.txt
--MyBoundary--

### Get notifications
GET {{RemoteControlApi_HostAddress}}/api/notifications

### Clear notifications
POST {{RemoteControlApi_HostAddress}}/api/notifications/clear

### Stream notifications (SSE)
GET {{RemoteControlApi_HostAddress}}/api/notifications/stream

### Report device version
POST {{RemoteControlApi_HostAddress}}/api/devices/device123/version
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "version": "1.0.0",
  "cardCode": "CARD123",
  "userName": "alice"
}

### Fetch pending notifications for device
GET {{RemoteControlApi_HostAddress}}/api/devices/device123/notifications

### Mark notification as read
POST {{RemoteControlApi_HostAddress}}/api/devices/device123/notifications/{notificationId}/read
